line_1: As when the furious tempest is o'erblown,
line_2: Yet the keen pang, the agony is gone;

line_1: Thus, the rude tempest of the field o'er-blown,
line_2: Shall whiter rounds of smiling years roll on:

line_1: A bold commander; but, the storm o'erblown,
line_2: He seem'd as he were made for peace alone;
Life's voyage to the world unknown.
